ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a good way to get involved with a lab. If you're a senior, you probably have to take this anyway.
It's research for credit, not a class per se. The lab you're in and project you're involved with are all that matter.
Great way to get credit for lab work. I think it goes without saying that how much you enjoy this class is directly related to your interest in your research and your relationship with your mentor.
Doing research for a credit is a great experience!
If you have a lab and you like, you should take research for credit! It will help you present your research and come up with new ideas for senior year.
